31/07/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Nine people died on Thursday (July 30th) after two cars and two trucks collided on a highway in southern Turkey, near the town of Tarsus. The sole survivor, a child, was seriously injured.
In other news, a moderate earthquake measuring 4.9 on the Richter scale rattled eastern Turkey, near the town of Erzincan. A second one, measuring 3.2, soon followed. No injuries or damage was reported. (AFP, Turkish Weekly, Anadolu news agency, Xinhua - 30/07/09) 
